claim.claim-text:
1. A liquid crystal display (LCD) comprising:
a substrate,
first and second pixel rows formed on the substrate and comprising a plurality of pixels, the plurality of pixels comprising a plurality of pairs of pixels, the pairs of pixels comprising two adjacent pixels in a pixel row;
a first gate line extending in a row direction on the substrate and connected with the first pixel row;
a second gate line extending in the row direction on the substrate, connected with the first pixel row;
a third gate line extending in the row direction on the substrate, connected with the second pixel row, and adjacent to the second gate line;
a fourth gate line extending in the row direction on the substrate, connected with the second pixel row;
a plurality of data lines extending in a column direction on the substrate, wherein the data lines are disposed every two of the pixels;
a first gate driver connected with the first and fourth gate lines, for applying gate signals to the first and fourth gate lines; and
a second gate driver connected with the second and third gate lines, for applying gate signals to the second and third gate lines,
wherein a part of a data line is disposed between two adjacent pairs of pixels and the data line is connected to only one pair of pixels of the two adjacent pairs of pixels, wherein no data line is present between the two pixels of the one pair.

5. A liquid crystal display (LCD) comprising:
a substrate,
a plurality of first and second pixel rows formed on the substrate and comprising a plurality of pixels, the plurality of pixels comprising a plurality of pairs of pixels, the pairs of pixels comprising two adjacent pixels in a pixel row;
a group of first gate lines connected with the first pixel row and comprising a first upper gate line and a first lower gate line;
a group of second gate lines connected with the second pixel row and comprising a second upper gate line and a second lower gate line;
a plurality of data lines extending in a column direction on the substrate, wherein each of the data lines are disposed every two of the pixels;
a first gate driver connected with the first upper gate line and the second lower gate line; and
a second gate driver connected with the first lower gate line and the second upper gate line,
wherein part of a data line is disposed between two adjacent pairs of pixels and the data line is connected to only one pair of pixels of the two adjacent pairs of pixels,
wherein two of the pixels adjacent in a column direction are connected to a different one of the data lines.

13. A method of forming an LCD panel, comprising:
forming a substrate;
forming a first row of pixels on the substrate;
forming a first gate line above the first row of pixels and a second gate line below the first row of pixels, wherein the first gate line and the second gate line are each connected to the first row of pixels;
forming a second row of pixels on the substrate;
forming a third gate line above the second row of pixels and a fourth gate line below the second row of pixels, wherein the third gate line and the fourth gate line are each connected to the second row of pixels;
forming a plurality of data lines on the substrate in columns, wherein each of the data lines is disposed every two pixels of the first row of pixels;
forming a first gate driver connected with the first and fourth gate lines; and
forming a second gate driver connected with the second and third gate lines,
wherein the pixels comprises a plurality of pairs of pixels, wherein the pairs of pixels comprises two adjacent pixels in a pixel row, and wherein a part of a data line is disposed between two adjacent pairs of pixels and the data line is connected to only one pair of pixels of the two adjacent pairs of pixels,
wherein the part is adjacent a part of a lower side of one pixel of one of the pairs it is connected to and adjacent an entire lower side of the other pixel of the one pair.
